summary: As the season gets closer and the cast does more promo work, you’re going to see a lot more of the usual, “Sansa is such a...
body:
As the season gets closer and the cast does more promo work, you’re going to see a lot more of the usual,

“Sansa is such a bitch!” “Sansa is going to betray everyone!” “Sansa is going to die!”

So I want to say just a little reminder that Sansa is going to survive the show. Sansa is going to be the driving force behind the North rebuilding and becoming stronger than ever. Sansa is the key person keeping the Vale, the North, and the Riverlands grouped together. Sansa values her family above all else and will do anything to protect them.

summary: i don't mind that people dislike sansa. i dislike many characters myself. the problem is that they don't just dislike sansa and...
body: i don’t mind that people dislike sansa. i dislike many characters myself. the problem is that they don’t just dislike sansa and be done with it. they invent reasons for their dislike by exaggerating events or making shit up. they delight in the awful things that happened to her. that’s where my defensiveness comes from, not from my insecurities (same as other sansa fans).

body: sansa is both inherently a good person and something she works hard to maintain. she fights her fear to protect and comfort those who have no one who would do so like dontos and the hound. she does it easily it while complimenting a sick lancel. she does it grudgingly while taking care of her sick cousin. that’s the strength of her character, that she has multiple reasons for having empathy and acting on it.

summary: you ship sansa x Willas? Arebt you a hypocrite about the age gap? they have a bigger one than Rhaegar x lynnna.
question: you ship sansa x Willas? Arebt you a hypocrite about the age gap? they have a bigger one than Rhaegar x lynnna.
answer:
I ship Sansa x Willas because it is the best canonical ship to get her out of Lannister hands and into a decent man who will not rape her (the series gives me low standards). Willas Tyrell is a well loved, well read man with crippled leg and a fascination with hounds and hawks. No one has anything bad to say about him. Not even Cersei.

My caveat is Willas Tyrell doesn’t rape his underage bride, lets Sansa grow up, and nurtures her (all this is fanon).

Willas Tyrell is basically a wish fulfilment.

Also Willas Tyrell isn’t a married father of two; isn’t dishonoring Sansa into bearing his bastard while making war on her family, and locking her up in a bloody tower.

Interesting even if Lyanna was of legal age (book or modern), Rhaegar would still be committing multiple felonies by kidnapping and raping her.
